Silty brown deposit east of arch 8237 and west of floor 8317.
CERAMICS_OBSERVATIONS: Many ceramics show evidence of burning, including soot that came off during washing, bubbled surfaces, and altered coloration of fabrics. High amounts of creamware and painted creamware, as well as African sigillatas with fugitive slip. Many fragments also covered with mortar, encrustations that are green and white, and black spotting (possibly soot or possibly mold), as well as occasional iron encrustations. Fragmentation varies between large and quite small fragments, often within a single class. Thin walled ware includes glass paste insets in two fragments.
